  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Patients with WHO Group I Pulmonary Arterial Hypertension from US based PAH centers.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Newly diagnosed or previously diagnosed patients with WHO Group I PAH.

          -  Documentation of the following hemodynamic parameters by right heart catheterization,
             performed at any time prior to study enrollment:

          -  Mean pulmonary arterial pressure (mPAP) &gt;25 mm Hg at rest or mPAP &gt; 30 mm Hg with
             exercise contemporaneous with a pulmonary wedge pressure ≤ 18 mm Hg

          -  Pulmonary wedge pressure ≤ 18 mm Hg

          -  Pulmonary vascular resistance (PVR) ≥ 240 dynes.sec.cm-5 (i.e., ≥ 3.0 Wood units)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who meet the criteria for inclusion into WHO Groups II, III, IV or V

          -  Have not had documentation of hemodynamic criteria for PAH by right heart
             catheterization at some time preceding study entry and following development of
             symptoms associated with PAH.

          -  Do not meet the required hemodynamic criteria for entry into the study
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
